#. <section class="sutta" id="sn20.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn20.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 20"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 20"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn20.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Opammavagga"
msgstr "1. Similes"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Biḷārasutta → biḷālasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn20.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Biḷārasutta"
msgstr "10. A Cat"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn20.10:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a certain junior mendicant socialized with families too "
"often."

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "The mendicants said to him:"

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.4"
msgid "“māyasmā ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, don’t socialize with families too often.”"

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.5"
msgid "So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno na viramati."
msgstr "But that mendicant, when spoken to by the mendicants, did not stop."

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te "
"bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"And then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said:"

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.7"
msgid "“idha, bhante, aññataro bhikkhu ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.8"
msgid "Tamenaṃ bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.9"
msgid "‘māyasmā ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn20.10:1.10"
msgid "So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno na viramatī”ti."
msgstr ""

# mudumusi here = musika in MN 50.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.271"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: biḷāro → biḷālo (bj) | viḷāro (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn20.10:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, biḷāro sandhisamalasaṅkaṭīre ṭhito ahosi mudumūsiṃ "
"maggayamāno:"
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, a cat was standing by an alley or a drain or "
"a dustbin hunting a little mouse:"

msgctxt "sn20.10:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘yadāyaṃ mudumūsi gocarāya pakkamissati, tattheva naṃ gahetvā khādissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When that little mouse comes out to feed, I’ll catch it right there and eat "
"it!’"

msgctxt "sn20.10:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mudumūsi gocarāya pakkāmi."
msgstr "And then that little mouse came out to feed."

#. VAR: saṅkhāditvā → asaṃkhāditvā (bj) | maṃsaṃ khāditvā (s1-3, km) | saṅkharitvā (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn20.10:2.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ biḷāro gahetvā sahasā saṅkhāditvā ajjhohari."
msgstr "The cat caught it and hastily swallowed it without chewing."

msgctxt "sn20.10:2.5"
msgid "Tassa so mudumūsi antampi khādi, antaguṇampi khādi."
msgstr "And that little mouse ate its intestines and mesentry,"

msgctxt "sn20.10:2.6"
msgid "So tatonidānaṃ maraṇampi nigacchi maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ."
msgstr "resulting in death and deadly pain."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn20.10:3.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā "
"pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena "
"arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena, anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā, asaṃvutehi "
"indriyehi."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, take a certain monk who robes up in the morning and, taking "
"his bowl and robe, enters the village or town for alms without guarding "
"body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without "
"restraining the sense faculties."

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.2"
msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā."
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes."

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti."
msgstr "Lust infects his mind,"

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.4"
msgid ""
"So rāgānuddhaṃsena cittena maraṇaṃ vā nigacchati maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ."
msgstr "resulting in death or deadly pain."

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.5"
msgid ""
"Maraṇañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye yo sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya "
"hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr ""
"For it is death in the training of the noble one to reject the training and "
"return to a lesser life."

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.6"
msgid ""
"Maraṇamattañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ aññataraṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ "
"āpajjati."
msgstr "And it is deadly pain to commit one of the corrupt offences"

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.7"
msgid "Yathārūpāya āpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyati."
msgstr "for which rehabilitation is possible."

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.8"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.9"
msgid ""
"‘rakkhiteneva kāyena rakkhitāya vācāya rakkhitena cittena, upaṭṭhitāya "
"satiyā, saṃvutehi indriyehi gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will enter the village or town for alms guarding body, speech, and mind, "
"establishing mindfulness, and restraining the sense faculties.’"

msgctxt "sn20.10:3.10"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn20.10:3.11"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
